com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.event

Interface CacheSessionEvent


  • public interface CacheSessionEvent
    An object with the CacheSessionEvent interface is returned by CacheSessionHandle.getCacheSessionEvent(). It is expected that applications will only call this method from the CacheSession onCacheSessionEvent(). The event callback is only invoked for asynchronous cache requests.
    • The CacheSessionEvent instance is mutable, it always represents the latest cache session event data as it is reused when new events occur.
    • Client applications should call CacheSessionHandle.takeCacheSessionEvent() to get a cloned copy of the last CacheSessionEvent
    .
